                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14653269" author="mbalassi" created="Tue, 4 Aug 2015 08:27:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;These tests share the basic setup and both of the reported failures are based on missing messages. I could not reproduce the failures locally.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hopefully it is a test issue, but it is still bothersome as it is testing the streaming fault tolerance after all.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14653386" author="stephanewen" created="Tue, 4 Aug 2015 10:00:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Interestingly, we are not observing any failures in the &lt;tt&gt;StateCheckpointedITCase&lt;/tt&gt;, so I assume it is a test issue.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It is super frequently occurring right now, so fixing this should have a priority.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14653398" author="mbalassi" created="Tue, 4 Aug 2015 10:10:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=sewen&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;sewen&quot;&gt;sewen&lt;/a&gt; Sure, I am touching that code anyway right now. Now I have observed the failure locally too.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;By the way: If I understand it correctly the difference between the `StateCheckpointedITCase` and the `StreamCheckpointingITCase` is that the former supposedly only uses the `Checkpointed` interface and not the `OperatorState` interface. Was that the intention, because it is currently not true? &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/flink/blob/master/flink-tests/src/test/java/org/apache/flink/test/checkpointing/StateCheckpoinedITCase.java#L299&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/flink/blob/master/flink-tests/src/test/java/org/apache/flink/test/checkpointing/StateCheckpoinedITCase.java#L299&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14653417" author="stephanewen" created="Tue, 4 Aug 2015 10:24:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The assumption was that the &lt;tt&gt;Checkpointed&lt;/tt&gt; interface is used in all situation: Source, chained, after a local channel + chained, after repartitioning.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It is true that I overlooked one place during the conversion. If you want to fix this, go ahead. Otherwise, I&apos;ll try to patch it later...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14653479" author="mbalassi" created="Tue, 4 Aug 2015 11:38:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed the oversight in &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;, the question mainly was about the purpose of the test.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/980&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/980&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14658394" author="stephanewen" created="Wed, 5 Aug 2015 15:38:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think I caught the issue in a pending fix, which improves the resource release in the barrier buffer.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14658639" author="stephanewen" created="Wed, 5 Aug 2015 18:24:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed via d738430cb7e26b5e31d953efa5e0036082d8de6e as a collateral of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-2484&quot; title=&quot;BarrierBuffer does not properly clean up temp files&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-2484&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-2484&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14704273" author="sachingoel0101" created="Thu, 20 Aug 2015 04:28:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Observed another failure. &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://travis-ci.org/apache/flink/jobs/76396571&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://travis-ci.org/apache/flink/jobs/76396571&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14711194" author="stephanewen" created="Tue, 25 Aug 2015 12:42:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed via 5aa70f70846f021b384c005b3dd3fd5ee3424d00&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
